content: Malaysian and Indonesian fritter **Jemput-jemput** or **cekodok** is a traditional [fritter](/wiki/Fritter) popular in [Malaysia](/wiki/Malaysia), [Brunei](/wiki/Brunei), [Indonesia](/wiki/Indonesia) and [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore) that is made from [wheat flour](/wiki/Wheat_flour). It is usually round in shape and tends to vary in size. There are many varieties of this snack, some using banana, [anchovies](/wiki/Anchovies) or [prawns](/wiki/Prawns), [onion](/wiki/Onion) or [maize](/wiki/Maize). - Food portal - Indonesia portal - Malaysia portal - Singapore portal This [Indonesian cuisine](/wiki/Indonesian_cuisine)-related article is a stub.
